  "text": "<div style=\"color:#cbd5e1;font-size:13px;line-height:1.6;padding:8px;\"><p>ⓘ This tab is for <b style=\"color:#f1f5f9;\">Electricity only</b>. We suggest using <b style=\"color:#f1f5f9;\">at least 2 years</b> of data to get more accurate estimation of the correlation between consumption and weather.</p><br/><p>- Very high correlation: changes of temperature directly impact the consumption.</p><p>- Correlation around 0: not much sensitivity.</p><p>- Correlation around -1: hotter and colder days inversely impact consumption.</p><br/><p style=\"color:#94a3b8;\">If all data shows up as zero degree days, it is an indicator that weather recording is inactive. Please contact your Pear customer success manager for more information.</p></div>",
